@startuml
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam BoxPadding 12
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam SequenceGroupBodyBackgroundColor #F5F5F5
skinparam ParticipantPadding 40
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 120
skinparam sequenceArrowFontSize 11
skinparam ParticipantFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderThickness 1.5

title D5 - Flexibility Forecasting (AI / Ollama)\nextension of Flexibility MS

participant "Camunda\n(Sprint 2)" as CAM
participant "Telemetry\nMS" as TMS
participant "Flexibility MS\nentity: FlexibilityEvent" as FEM
database "AWS RDS\n(Flexibility MS)" as DB
participant "Ollama LLM\n(AWS EC2\nport 11434)" as AI
participant "Kafka\n4.1.1" as K

note over CAM,TMS
Sprint 1: direct REST call
Sprint 2: Camunda via Kong REST Connector
Ollama is an internal extension — no separate MS,
no separate RDS, no separate Kafka topic
end note

== Cross-entity logic (Camunda responsibility) ==

CAM -> TMS : GET /telemetry/history\n?gridCellId=X&limit=100
TMS --> CAM : [historical telemetry records\nwith soc_percent, active_power_kw...]

CAM -> FEM : POST /flexibility-events/forecast\n{gridCellId, telemetryLogs}

== Flexibility MS: internal AI-extended logic ==

FEM -> DB : SELECT past_flexibility_events\nWHERE status IN (EXECUTED, FAILED)\nORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 100
DB --> FEM : [past event logs\nwith offerType, result, timestamp]

FEM -> AI : POST /api/generate\n{model: "llama3",\nstream: false,\nprompt: "Analyse flexibility logs.\nRate grid success 0.0 to 1.0.\nIdentify key patterns."}

AI --> FEM : {response: "POSITIVE sentiment.\nSuccess rate: 0.82.\nPattern: SoC>90% discharge\nduring peak hours effective.",\ndone: true}

FEM -> FEM : Parse AI response\nExtract success_rate,\nsentiment, aiPattern

== Persist and publish (same RDS and topic as D2) ==

FEM -> DB : INSERT flexibility_event\n{offerType: AI_DISCHARGE,\nsentiment: POSITIVE,\nsuccessRate: 0.82,\naiPattern: "SoC>90% peak",\ntimestamp: now()}

FEM -> K : produce to Flexibility Event topic\n{offerType: AI_DISCHARGE,\nsuccessRate: 0.82,\naiPattern: "SoC>90% peak"}

FEM --> CAM : 201 Created\n{flexibilityEventId}

@enduml
